### Swift Enums

Enumerations (enums) define a common type for a group of related values. Swift enums are more powerful than in most languages - they can have methods, computed properties, initializers, and associated values.

**Basic Enum Syntax:**

```swift
enum Direction {
    case north
    case south
    case east
    case west
}

// Compact form
enum CompassPoint { case north, south, east, west }

// Usage
var direction = Direction.north
direction = .west  // Type inference after assignment

switch direction {
case .north: print("Going north")
case .south: print("Going south")
case .east: print("Going east")
case .west: print("Going west")
}
```

**Enum with Methods and Properties:**

```swift
enum Planet: Int {
    case mercury = 1, venus, earth, mars

    // Computed property
    var surfaceGravity: Double {
        switch self {
        case .earth: return 9.8
        case .mars: return 3.7
        case .venus: return 8.9
        case .mercury: return 3.7
        }
    }

    // Method
    func description() -> String {
        return "Planet \(self) with gravity \(surfaceGravity) m/s²"
    }
}

print(Planet.earth.description())
```

**Enum Features:**

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Raw values | Default values for each case |
| Associated values | Attach extra data to cases |
| Methods | Functions inside enum |
| Computed properties | Properties that compute values |
| Initializers | Custom init methods |
| Protocol conformance | Enums can conform to protocols |
| Recursive enums | Enums that reference themselves |

```swift
// Iterating all cases
enum Beverage: CaseIterable {
    case coffee, tea, juice, water
}

for drink in Beverage.allCases {
    print(drink)
}
```

> **Key Point:** Swift enums are first-class types. They can have computed properties, methods, initializers, and conform to protocols - just like classes and structs.

Enums with raw values automatically get a failable initializer `init?(rawValue:)` to create an instance from a raw value.

codeExample:
import Foundation

enum TrafficLight {
    case red, yellow, green

    var duration: Int {
        switch self {
        case .red: return 30
        case .yellow: return 5
        case .green: return 25
        }
    }

    func description() -> String {
        "Light is \(self) for \(duration) seconds"
    }

    mutating func next() {
        switch self {
        case .red: self = .green
        case .yellow: self = .red
        case .green: self = .yellow
        }
    }
}

var light = TrafficLight.red
print(light.description())
light.next()
print(light.description())
light.next()
print(light.description())

// CaseIterable
enum Suit: String, CaseIterable {
    case hearts, diamonds, clubs, spades
}

print("\nAll suits:")
for suit in Suit.allCases {
    print(suit.rawValue.capitalized)
}
